lwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=sadidas>Sadidas</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/15/03 8:02 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Why a monk for RT?</span><hr size=1> Before a series of patches, I always had the RB functioning as the first person on the RB list that had all forms of attack off (disarm,kick, auto attack, right clicks, taunt).  That worked to perfection for several weeks, with no variation, but had limited testing to velious encounters, ie vindi.<br>
<br>
<br>
I ve seen other mobs switch after 30 seconds or so (RumbleCrush),  with everyone meleeing for at least 20 secs.   I believe rampage list order changes, with healing being the Huge*  list movement enhancer.   Again, by keeping healers out of the rampage range, you wont ever see it.   Pallies and sks can be a problem with rampage with their group spells, as can support melee with low delay mainhand weapons.<br>
<br>
I ve tested telling RBs to maintain melee on the mob with slower weapons for the first 30 secs, and switching to their normal dps gear afterwards.   This seems to hold RB steady, with neither pallies or sks getting nailed for their group and single target heals, nor having the RB take aggro based on greater dps and similar proximity to the Target Mob.<br>
<br>
<br>
I m wondering if the RB can be locked after you attain a certain amount of aggro points... ie, you reach "2000" pts of aggro, you lock  into an RB list position among other players that have surpassed "2000" pts of aggro.  This would be kind of a tertiary list, (Main aggro list,  Altered Aggro List, Final Rampage List).  Ideally, you get your chosen RB to the " 2000" pt first and foremost.  Then that character could sit idle with auto attack off, and avoid any chance of taking aggro (or continue to melee, if he has any clue at all).  The CH rotation healers would likely reach the 2000 pt aggro mark faster than most RBs could safely through melee.  Again, proximity control!<br>
<br>
Just thoughts... poor vindi is gonna die like a fiend until I get some better testing done. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000000><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub14.ezboard.com/bthesteelwarrior.showUserPublicProfile?gid=laeninraidge>Laenin Raidge</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://147.4.150.5/~jercole1/laenin.jpg" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>knows that Warriors are superior</span><br>  Posts: 1<br> <font color=#FF0000>(2/19/03 2:52 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Quick Question</span><hr size=1> Quick 2 questions . . .<br>
